    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46), an icon of naturally aspirated performance. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. This example features the desirable 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a limited-slip variable M differential for precise power distribution. Significant preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rear subframe reinforcement and recent valve lash adjustments. The suspension retains its factory geometry with refreshed bushings, ensuring the chassis remains composed under high lateral loads. While the aesthetic reflects its status as a driven machine, its mechanical vitals are robust, making it a prime candidate for the purist seeking a balanced, high-revving driver.",
